reviews.headline: Great for both top and bottom lashes
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This is very buildable and I love how tiny the applicator was. It's prefect for top and bottom lashes. Felt kinda drying but lasts a long time

reviews.headline: Irritates Eyes
reviews.comments: Love the brush it reaches the smallest eyelash , however the formula really irritated my eyes the fall out was a lot. at the end of the day I looked like a racoon it seems like it melted into my skin.

reviews.headline: Long lasting non-flaking formula with long lashes
reviews.comments: This is a great formula and my new go-to mascara! There was no fallout and it made my lashes look naturally long with great volume.

reviews.headline: Best

reviews.headline: I would say I got an expired product
reviews.comments: It took three coats to even show up, and about eight to even look like different. Its appearance was dull with no shine. The mascara was dry, like it was missing moisture. reviews.comments: Terrible product! I ordered as a replacement for my regular mascara which wasn't going to come in time for my vacation. The product is thick, clumpy and difficult to remove. The wand came apart after only a couple of uses.

reviews.headline: Much prefer Estee Lauder's mascara
reviews.comments: I originally was looking for Estee Lauder's Double Wear mascara. I was told that Ulta did not stock it and the sales associate suggested Lancome was a close alternative. I've never had a mascara smudge so much. Totally embarrassing to have raccoon eyes in public.

reviews.headline: Best Mascara
reviews.comments: I'm very picky about mascara. My go-to's are always drugstore. In my experience,  high-end usually flakes or smudges and I can't stand that especially when paying a high price, but this mascara has set a new bar for me. It's easy to apply, lasts all day, and really lengthens and defines my lashes in the best way. Plus, who knew mascara tubes could be so cute? I'm in love, and will buy it even if it's not on sale.

reviews.headline: racoon eyes
reviews.comments: This mascara gave me racoon eyes and was running within the hour. it wasn't hot or humid and there was black residue unde my eyes.

reviews.headline: By far my favorite high end mascara
reviews.comments: This mascara is literally my new favorite high end mascara. I love how it leaves my lashes , it doesn't leave them clumpy . It makes my lashes look like if I have a lot and very fluffy .

reviews.headline: Love this mascara!!
reviews.comments: I love this mascara! Doesn't flake or smir under the eye during wear. Adds length and separates lashes! I wear this one everyday and would recommend.

reviews.headline: Love, Love this product ü©∑
reviews.comments: I can't say enough about this product! I use the Lanc√¥me primer then apply Lanc√¥me Flutter. I've been asked numerous times if my lashes are my own! Easy to apply!

reviews.headline: Lashes for Days
reviews.comments: I have naturally decent lashes to start with, but this mascara really does the trick. I use the Cils Booster XL and get a great outcome. My lashes come out long, thick, and it doesn't bleed into my concealer like most of the other formulas. I've been using Lanc√¥me mascara since high school, and I love this formula. If you want drama, here it is.

reviews.headline: Mix emotions
reviews.comments: I have a love and hate relationship with this mascara it gives me what i want but it stains after a few minutes

reviews.headline: Lengthening Mascara ‚Äì Great for Everyday Wear!
reviews.comments:
I received this as a free sample, and I was really impressed with how well it performed! The Lanc√¥me Lash Idole Flutter Mascara does exactly what it promises‚Äîadds visible length and gives your lashes a soft, fluttery effect. It's super lightweight and doesn't clump, flake, or smudge throughout the day, even after hours of wear.

I love how natural yet enhanced my lashes look. It's perfect for a polished daytime look or as a base if you want to build up more drama with other products. My only small critique is that it doesn't provide as much volume as I personally prefer, but for length and comfort, it's fantastic.

Definitely a great choice if you're looking for a clean, lengthening formula that lasts. I'll be adding this to my collection!

reviews.headline: Lengthening
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I have always loved Lanc√¥me Masacaras! I usually used the idole mascara but this one is just as good! It's super lengthening without being clumpy. It dries down very quick but I would wait to use a setting spray until it's dry as it does smudge with a setting spray.

reviews.headline: Great Everyday Mascara
reviews.comments: Lancome Lash Idole Flutter Mascara might be one of the best mascaras I've ever tried. I was a little apprehensive when I saw the tiny bristles on the wand, but they did a great job of coating my lashes. This mascara is super easy to apply and makes my lashes look full. It really adds volume and length. It was also easy to remove with my everyday cleanser. (I received this product for free in exchange for my honest review.)

reviews.headline: Tubing mascara
reviews.comments: It's a tubing macara, super easy to remove!

reviews.headline: love this mascara
reviews.comments: I love this mascara, it is my go to now. It creates so much volume and the perfect lash curl. It is so easy to apply and just as easy to remove.

faceoff_positive.comments: Ok so first off we are going to ignore the eczema around my eyes please and thanks. But OH MY GOD !!! I have no benefit in lying to you, I'm not an influencer trying to market something to you for own personal interests. THIS IS WONDERFUL! I have straight thick black lashes, relatively hard to get to hold a curl with mascaras. They're heavy. This is a wonderfully perfect consistence of a wet formula but dries quick enough to hold the curl without making my lashes fall too quickly. I am actually shocked at how well this separated my lashes with the wand alone. I expected it to be similar to L'Or√©al telescopic, but this is not a drugstore product and it really does have the quality of its value. So imagine a high-end higher performing telescopic if you like that one. This is my actual new fave and I'm going to grab this one first before my other mascaras! I'm so excited about it. The formula is so smooth and it glided on. I don't do multiple coats like some people it's never worked for me. I just apply layer and layer all at once until I'm happy with the product distributed. This BUILT UP! Like it was a buildable formula and it gave me slight volume but the LENGTH!!! I haven't had a mascara make my lashes look this long since when I was experimenting with make up in high school. I'm so happy about this mascara. I hope when you try it and it works as amazing as it did for me!!!! It really wow'ed me. It's not waterproof either which really makes it easier to take off at night, i much more prefer this formula. When brushing from root to tip, I can feel the product evenly distributing and it shows when it adds that length to the tip! Wow. And lastly, NO CLUMPS? The bristles are so fine and there are so many. I was shocked after the first swipe at how it glided without clumping even after multiple swipes. I'm so impressed!
faceoff_positive.headline: The formula! The length!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I had high hopes for the Lanc√¥me Lash Idole Flutter Extension Mascara, but unfortunately, it didn't quite live up to my expectations.  

What I Liked:
One of the standout features of this mascara is the thin wand, which makes application incredibly easy‚Äîespecially for those of us with small, hooded eyes. Unlike bulkier wands that can be difficult to maneuver, this one allows for precise application, reaching every lash without smudging product all over the lids. I also appreciated how well it separated my lashes, avoiding the dreaded clumpy look that some mascaras create.  

What I Didn't Like:
While the wand excels at separation, the formula itself left a lot to be desired. No matter how many layers I applied, my lashes still looked almost bare. While it's true that you can build a few coats without it clumping, the tradeoff is that it doesn't add length, volume, or hold a curl‚Äîall essential qualities for a good mascara. Even just two hours in, it looked like I wasn't wearing any mascara at all. Given the wand's slim design, I wasn't expecting much volume, but the complete lack of impact was disappointing.  Perhaps a waterproof version might give more hold and curl.

If you're looking for a mascara that gives a natural, barely-there look with great separation, this might work for you. However, if you need any sort of drama, lift, or hold, this formula simply won't cut it. For my small, hooded eyes, the wand was perfect, but the results just weren't there.
faceoff_negative.headline: Disappointing
